						<summary>

						<p>Broken slab set up under a tree near the <hi rend="italic">nīrukōna</hi> about 3 km to the north of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Chitrabhānu, Śrāvaṇa ba. 2, Friday.</hi> It may be assigned to the 18th century in which case the details regularly correspond to 1762 A.D., August 2.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a well in Nāgāyapalle probably near Chīmalapeṇṭa by a certain China-Tāṭireḍḍi son of Peddaya and grand son of Ami-reḍḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
